-- GDF Suez Confirms Williamson Project Leader, Corporate Finance
-- B y   C a r o l   M a t l a c k
-- 2011-12-22T19:45:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/gdf-suez-confirms-williamson-project-leader-corporate-finance.html
GDF Suez,  France ’s largest natural-
gas producer, confirmed that Mark Williamson, chief financial
officer of International Power, has been appointed as project
leader on its corporate finance team, effective May 15.  Geert Peeters, senior vice president and chief financial
officer of the company’s Global Gas and LNG business line, is to
become deputy CFO of International Power in January and then CFO
in May, the Paris-based utility said in an e-mailed statement.  Benoit Mignard, director of acquisition investment and
financial advisory of GDF Suez, will replace Peeters as CFO of
the Global Gas and LNG business line, while Didier Engels, the
group’s planning and controlling director, will become CFO of
the Energy Europe business line, GDF Suez said.  Pierre Chareyre, now chief executive officer of GDF Suez
Trading, is to become deputy CFO of GDF Suez on Feb. 15.
Sebastien Arbola, currently in charge of mergers and
acquisitions reporting to Mignard, on May 15 will become mergers
and acquisitions director reporting directly to GDF Suez
Executive Vice President and CFO Isabelle Kocher.  To contact the reporter on this story:
